# Summary

<div class="block">

![Convergent Sequence](/img/graphs/calculus/monotonic-sequence-theorem.png)

The use of convergence and divergence apply in a variety of different settings, such as functions, sequences, 
and integrals, etc. Though definitions are slightly different depending on context, convergence generally tends
to mean values become closer and closer to some specified limit, and divergence tends to mean the contextual
object in question is not converging.

</div>

